25|$|UNBRO also {{supervised}} {{the provision of}} water in the border camps, few of which had access to natural sources of potable water. Each week trucks supplied by the Thai government transported 650,000 liters of chlorinated water to storage tanks <b>in</b> <b>the</b> <b>camps.</b> In addition, UNBRO supplied building materials to refugees and implemented an agricultural program to produce fresh vegetables <b>in</b> <b>the</b> <b>camps.</b>|$|E
